MemberSignature.Value: member this.TimezoneId : string with get, set

Docs.summary: Id of the timezone. Allowed values are timezones supported by Windows. Windows keeps details on supported timezones, including the id, in registry under KEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Time Zones. You can get those registry values via SQL Server by querying SELECT name AS timezone_id FROM sys.time_zone_info. List of Ids can also be obtained by executing [System.TimeZoneInfo]::GetSystemTimeZones() in PowerShell. An example of valid timezone id is "Pacific Standard Time" or "W. Europe Standard Time".
